<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,781,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[151,379,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Material examined</emphasis>
: One female 
<number box="[555,621,781,807]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="183.1">183.1</number>
µm long, from Terras do Pico, Pico Island, mounted in Hoyer’s medium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,781,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
Apart from filament A (
<number box="[482,535,861,887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="37.3">37.3</number>
µm long), all lateral and dorsal appendages are spines: C, 
<number box="[1231,1283,861,887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="19.2">19.2</number>
µm long; D, 
<number box="[151,202,904,930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="19.5">19.5</number>
µm long; E, 
<number box="[356,407,904,930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="19.5">19.5</number>
µm long; C d, 
<number box="[572,609,904,930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="4.6">4.6</number>
µm long; and D d, 7.0 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,781,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
The species is considered cosmopolitan; the form 
<emphasis box="[780,962,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">brachyspinosus</emphasis>
in recorded from the Carpathians, North 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,984,1010]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">America</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[266,365,984,1010]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[422,583,984,1010]" name="New Zealand" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
